      "message": "This is not true, in terms of the current implementation.\nAlso, \"in the implementation\", I strongly recommend not to mix the test metadata that Test authors write, and actual test we run. They are in different domain.\nPractically, mixing them introduces a lot of assumption to many functions, so it makes them difficult to understand. It also makes it difficult to maintain because it makes it easier to misuse, like a function only for a test after expand to apply a test before expand. We should have different type for them at least internally.\n\nCould you avoid mentioning the concrete type name?",
